title: Invesco Electric Vehicle Metals Commodity Strategy No K-1 ETF (NASDAQ:EVMT) Shares Sold by Jane Street Group LLC
text: Jane Street Group LLC trimmed its holdings in Invesco Electric Vehicle Metals Commodity Strategy No K-1 ETF ( NASDAQ:EVMT – Free Report ) by 51.0% during the third quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm owned 18,124 shares of the company’s stock after selling 18,844 shares during the quarter. Jane Street Group LLC owned approximately 3.62% of Invesco Electric Vehicle Metals Commodity Strategy No K-1 ETF worth $300,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. Separately, Commonwealth Equity Services LLC grew its position in Invesco Electric Vehicle Metals Commodity Strategy No K-1 ETF by 25.1% in the 2nd quarter. Commonwealth Equity Services LLC now owns 26,587 shares of the company’s stock valued at $443,000 after buying an additional 5,335 shares during the last quarter. NASDAQ EVMT opened at $14.57 on Friday. Invesco Electric Vehicle Metals Commodity Strategy No K-1 ETF has a 52-week low of $14.47 and a 52-week high of $19.43. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $15.25 and a 200 day moving average price of $15.71. The firm also recently announced a dividend, which was paid on Friday, December 27th. Stockholders of record on Monday, December 23rd were paid a dividend of $0.5286 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend was Monday, December 23rd. ( Free Report )The Invesco Electric Vehicle Metals Commodity Strategy No K-1 ETF (EVMT) is an exchange-traded fund that mostly invests in broad market commodities. The fund is an actively managed fund consisting of commodity-linked futures and other financial instruments that provide exposure to the various metals used to produce electric vehicles.
